=09=09=09=09Counting on courts
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Al Gore went on fighting after two court decisions went against=
 him in his=20
bid to contest the result of the presidential vote-count in Florida. First,=
=20
the federal Supreme Court refused to uphold (or reject) the decision of the=
=20
Florida Supreme Court to extend the deadline for hand recounts, and sent th=
e=20
case back for the court to explain its reasons. The next day, a Florida=20
circuit court upheld the state=01,s results, giving George W. Bush a winnin=
g=20
margin of 537 votes. Mr Gore appealed against the ruling. Mr Gore was=20
encouraged by a federal appeals-court ruling that rejected Mr Bush=01,s req=
uest=20
to throw out the results of manual recounts in Florida.
=09=09=09=09See article: The fight for the presidencyE+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Meanwhile, Mr Bush tried to consolidate his probable position a=
s=20
president-elect. For the first time, he received an intelligence briefing=
=20
from the CIA. He told his aides in Texas, however, that they should continu=
e=20
calling him =01&Mr Governor=018.=20
=09=09=09=09See article: George Bush=01,s awkward transition
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09There were rows in Chile over General Augusto Pinochet. A Chile=
an court=20
suspended procedures for his arrest on charges of murder and kidnapping,=20
pending his appeal, while President Ricardo Lagos met armed-forces chiefs t=
o=20
discuss the issue.
