=09=09=09=09Nice work
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Amid last-minute wrangling and violent protests by anti-globali=
sation=20
activists, leaders of the European Union=01,s 15 countries gathered in the=
=20
French city of Nice, where they hope to change the rules of the Union to=20
allow countries mainly from Central Europe to join. France said it was=20
reluctant to let the EU=01,s voting system be changed so that Germany would=
 have=20
a bigger say in EU decisions.=20
=09=09=09=09See article: Will the EU expand?E+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Responding to EU plans for a rapid-reaction military force, Ame=
rica=01,s=20
outgoing defence secretary, William Cohen, said that NATO should not be=20
allowed to become a =01&relic of the past=018.
